@Hailei @gianm Yep, I was able to reproduce as well, and think you are correct about what is going on. 

I looked at #175 (which closes #145) and didn't actually see anything that addressed this issue. #2257 fixes a different case, so it would seem this bug is still present.

I think instead of checking for null in the Aggregator we can modify RowboatMergeFunction.apply 

```
  for (int i = 0; i < metrics.length; ++i) {
      Object lhsMetric = lhsMetrics[i];
      Object rhsMetric = rhsMetrics[i];
      if (lhsMetric == null) {
          metrics[i] = rhsMetric;
      } else if (rhsMetric == null) {
          metrics[i] = lhsMetric;
      } else {
          metrics[i] = metricAggs[i].combine(lhsMetric, rhsMetric);
      }
  }
```

This avoids having to modify every aggregator type.

``` java
